(1, 3, 17, 'Environment Structure'),
(2, 3, 17, 'This page presents general information about the TelEduc environment, its tools and their uses.'),
(3, 3, 17, 'Access Authentication'),
(4, 3, 17, 'The environment has a system of course access authentication. In order for instructors, coordinators, students, collaborators and visitors to access the course, they need a password and a personal identification (login) which are requested each time the participant accesses the course.'),
(5, 3, 17, 'Attention! To guarantee the integrity of the information stored in the course it is essential to close the browser (Mozilla/Opera/Netscape Navigator/Microsoft Internet Explorer)  at the end of each access session.'),
(6, 3, 17, 'Course Homepage'),
(7, 3, 17, 'The course home page is divided into two parts. On the left are the tools that will be utilized during the course, and, on the right, is the content corresponding to the given tool currently selected from the list on the left. '),
(8, 3, 17, 'Upon entering the course, the content of the tool, "Agenda" is displayed, containing current information, hints or suggestions from the instructors for the students. This page serves as a channel of direct communication from the instructors to the students. Information is placed here that would normally be presented at the beginning of a face-to-face class. The content of the "Agenda" is updated according to the course dynamics.'),
(9, 3, 17, 'Each course supported by the TelEduc environment can utilize a subset of the tools described below. In this way, it may be that at any given moment in the course, some tools may not be visible in the left side menu, and, therefore, would be unavailable. Whether or not to offer a tool at varying points during the course is part of the methodology adopted by each instructor. Normally, the addition of a new tool is announced to the students in the Agenda.'),
(10, 3, 17, 'Tools in the environment'),
(11, 3, 17, 'The following tools are for the exclusive use of Instructors and the course Coordinator.'),
(12, 3, 17, 'GNU General Public License'),
(13, 3, 17, 'TelEduc is a free software  you may distribute it and/or modify it according to the terms of the'),
(14, 3, 17, 'version 2, as published by the Free Software Foundation.'),
(15, 3, 17, 'Final Observations'),
(16, 3, 17, 'TelEduc is an environment in development by the'),
(17, 3, 17, 'Nucleus of Informatics Applied to Education'),
(18, 3, 17, 'of the State University of Campinas'),
(19, 3, 17, 'How does the TelEduc environment work?'),
(20, 3, 17, 'Following installation of the environment on the server, it is recommended that one person be appointed environment Administrator.'),
(21, 3, 17, 'It is the Administrator`s responsibility to create instances of courses on the server. Requests are made by professionals who will assume the role of Coordinators of the courses hosted on this server. To create a course, the Administrator must be informed of the course name, the Coordinator`s name and his/her e-mail address. Once the instance of the course has been created, the system sends an e-mail to the Coordinator indicating his/her TelEduc access authentication (login and password).'),
(22, 3, 17, 'The Coordinator can then access the environment and actually open registration for the course, using the Administration tool, and register the course Instructor(s). This will enable the course to be posted on the page, Courses Open for Registration, on the given server. People interested in the course can, at this point, access the on-line registration form. Coordinator and Instructor(s) analyze the registration requests, which are accepted or rejected according to the selection criteria established by the institution responsible for the course offering. The candidates are notified via e-mail whether or not their registration was accepted. In the case of acceptance, the participant will receive his/her access authorization and can utilize the environment in the capacity of Student or Visitor (without visualization of the Administration tools).'),
(23, 3, 17, 'There are different types of course participants. Instructors and Coordinator are responsible for the planning and development of the course as a whole. (The Coordinator is a special type of Instructor who is responsible for certain course administrative functions.) Then there are the Students, some of whom may be classified as collaborators or visitors. Therefore, there are tools that are restricted to the Coordinator and/or Instructors, and others that are freely accessible to the students, except for collaborators or visitors.'),
(24, 3, 17, 'The following tools are described below: '),
(25, 3, 17, 'Tools with exclusive access by the instructors and coordinator only'),
